    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-18T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-18T07:00:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8817: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-18T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 18, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 18—11:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is reported that the Chinese and the Japanese reached an understanding here
                    this afternoon under which Sung Che Yuan expressed regret that some of his
                    subordinates had come into conflict with Japanese soldiers; agreed to punish a
                    few of his subordinates; stated that he was already attending to the suppression
                    of communism and anti-Japanese propaganda and agreed to the garrisoning of
                    Wanping-hsien by <hi rend="italic">Paoantui</hi>.<note n="36" xml:id="d194fn36"
                        >Local militia.</note>
                </p>
                <p>About 3,000 Japanese soldiers arrived here today from Shanhaikuan. Japanese have
                    occupied all railway stations and are preparing additional quarters for their
                    troops.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
